ing:**  Added to prevent exploding gradients, a common issue in RNNs/LSTMs.\n* **`reset_gradients()`:** Resets the gradients to zero before each training iteration.\n* **Training Loop:** Iterates over the training data (X_train, y_train) for a specified number of epochs.\n* **Loss Calculation (MSE):** Calculates the Mean Squared Error (MSE) as a measure of the model\u0027s performance.\n* **Reshape `y_train`:** Reshaped to be a column vector (n_samples, 1) for consistency.\n\nThis revised version provides a basic, trainable LSTM.  However, remember that this is a *simplified* LSTM.  A real-world LSTM would have more complex gating mechanisms (input gate, forget gate, output gate, cell state) and would be significantly more complex to implement from scratch. Using `TensorFlow` or `PyTorch` is strongly recommended for more realistic LSTM modeling.\n\nBy addressing these improvements, you can significantly enhance the capabilities of your code and make it more useful for analyzing financial data. Remember to focus on clearly defining the problem you are trying to solve and choosing the appropriate tools and techniques.\n",
